califont
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:a gas apparatus for heating water; a geyser
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1915 Mary O'Connor, Wellington ca1952 R. Mason In universal use in NZ for a certain type of gas hot water heater, for the English `geyser'? - a name never used in NZ. 1982 February. Jean Watson used it for an above-the-sink gas water-heater
